Nike Popoola An entrepreneur, Jessica Nwalozie, has emerged as the winner of the Vlisco Fashion Fund 2019 in Nigeria. A statement said her win would earn her €5,000, plus a two-week masterclass abroad. It stated that through the Vlisco Fashion Fund, a contest, emerging African fashion designers and their businesses based in Nigeria, DRC Congo, Benin, Togo, Ivory Coast and Ghana, were launched on a global scale. African fashion designers living outside Africa could also enter to compete in the global contestant category, it added. The statement said, “In 2019, one winner was selected from each of this year’s six participating countries, and one winner from the global category. “The seven winners will each receive career funding equivalent to €5,000, plus a two-week masterclass abroad.” It stated that more than 700 applications were submitted to the Vlisco Fashion Fund 2019. It also said the VFF team meticulously reviewed the eligible applications, and then the jury conducted interviews in each country. Based on the interviews, three nominees per country reportedly progressed to the next round. Copyright PUNCH.
